sentences: In 2011, Opera America awarded her their National Opera Trustee Award.

Caulkins earned her bachelor's degree at the University of Colorado Denver in 1977 after graduating Phi Beta Kappa.
In 2010, the university awarded her their Alumni Recognition Award.
The next year, the University of Colorado awarded her an honorary doctorate of humane letters.
In 1980, Caulkins and Dillon co-founded Friends of Opera as a volunteer group.
Two years after its founding, Friends of Opera's efforts merged into Opera Colorado, an opera company that facilitates performances and promotes education and outreach.
In 2006, Denver Mayor John Hickenlooper (then the Governor of Colorado) awarded Caulkins a Culture Legacy Award for her service to the city.
